The article is a transcript of speeches given by Prime Minister Kishida of Japan, Prime Minister Albanese of Australia, Prime Minister Modi of India, and President Biden of the United States at the Quad Summit held in Tokyo. The leaders discussed the importance of the Quad in promoting a free and open Indo-Pacific region, as well as addressing global and regional challenges such as the Russian invasion of Ukraine and climate change. They emphasized the need for cooperation and solidarity among Quad countries, as well as listening to the voices of other countries in the region. Each leader also highlighted their respective country's commitment to the Quad and their priorities for the future, including climate action, economic security, and strengthening partnerships in the Indo-Pacific.